1
00:00:03,078 --> 00:00:06,996
As I’ve mentioned many times, 
Rukmiṇī says

2
00:00:06,996 --> 00:00:09,996
śrutvā guṇān bhuvana-sundara śṛṇvatāṁ te
[SB: 10.52.37]

3
00:00:09,996 --> 00:00:13,255
Hearing about You …
She hasn’t met Kṛṣṇa yet.

4
00:00:13,777 --> 00:00:16,227
By hearing about Him though, 
she has.

5
00:00:16,273 --> 00:00:18,383
[ Sound Reveals Form ]

6
00:00:18,703 --> 00:00:20,970
Some conception 
has come to her

7
00:00:20,970 --> 00:00:24,760
about the form of Kṛṣṇa, 
His quality … everything.

8
00:00:24,760 --> 00:00:27,028
Her we take in a big way.

9
00:00:27,028 --> 00:00:29,638
We say, “Oh! It’s Rukmiṇī,
she’d knew Him before.

10
00:00:29,638 --> 00:00:33,108
It’s not like that. 
She had not met Him.

11
00:00:33,108 --> 00:00:36,478
The wives of the yajñic brahmins, 
the vipra-patnīs

12
00:00:36,478 --> 00:00:37,959
they hadn’t met Kṛṣṇa.

13
00:00:37,959 --> 00:00:41,209
They’d only heard about Him 
from fruit sellers.

14
00:00:41,209 --> 00:00:42,513
And others in Vrindavan

15
00:00:42,513 --> 00:00:47,663
they heard about Him, 
by hearing about Him, they got …

16
00:00:47,663 --> 00:00:51,189
See, you could have a general idea, 
but if you’ve realized

17
00:00:51,189 --> 00:00:54,073
at a particular advanced stage
of devotion, by hearing

18
00:00:54,073 --> 00:00:58,533
they are getting a very precise 
conception of the form.

19
00:00:58,533 --> 00:01:02,988
So it’s mysterious, 
acintya-bhedābheda—

20
00:01:02,988 --> 00:01:04,228
having not met,

21
00:01:04,228 --> 00:01:05,878
but through hearing 
they’re meeting,

22
00:01:05,878 --> 00:01:10,558
but it’s creating 
a hunger to meet.

23
00:01:11,578 --> 00:01:17,263
So that’s why we’re advised
to culture separation.

24
00:01:17,714 --> 00:01:21,652
And we say, “Well, if we haven’t met
how we can culture separation?”

25
00:01:21,652 --> 00:01:24,302
By hearing.

26
00:01:24,762 --> 00:01:27,762
The mystery is

27
00:01:27,762 --> 00:01:31,467
that by hearing about Kṛṣṇa
some conception comes to you.

28
00:01:31,477 --> 00:01:38,812
Whether vague, or more refined,
or substantial.

29
00:01:39,382 --> 00:01:46,342
And gradually, 
some hunger develops.

30
00:01:47,940 --> 00:01:53,970
Like, I mean 
a cheap example would be

31
00:01:53,970 --> 00:01:58,770
that in this world …
babies …

32
00:01:58,770 --> 00:02:02,630
they are hungry
before they’ve eaten.

33
00:02:06,660 --> 00:02:12,238
And than they’re fed.
So this is a mysterious thing.

34
00:02:12,238 --> 00:02:14,785
You say, “Well, how can 
you have the hunger?”

35
00:02:14,785 --> 00:02:19,495
Well, you can. 
You can awaken in you

36
00:02:19,495 --> 00:02:21,552
by hearing about Kṛṣṇa

37
00:02:21,552 --> 00:02:26,662
can awaken a hunger,
and a sense of loss.

38
00:02:26,662 --> 00:02:30,030
So beautiful,
and what’s been lost to me?

39
00:02:30,180 --> 00:02:32,320
Now it’s compelling.

40
00:02:35,230 --> 00:02:42,440
So, hunger in this sense
hunger precedes tasting

41
00:02:43,767 --> 00:02:50,217
and is a necessary component
for taste is hunger.

42
00:02:51,155 --> 00:02:57,185
So separation is the necessary component
for relishing union.

